questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot application deployed to an external Servlet container experiences a progressive memory leak in the JVM Heap after multiple hot redeployments. Eventually, the JVM crashes with an `OutOfMemoryError: Metaspace`. Upon analyzing a heap dump, you identify thousands of active instances of the application's WebappClassLoader holding onto thread-local variables. You isolate the following filter configuration:

java
@WebFilter("/*")
public class TenantFilter implements Filter {
    @Override
    public void doFilter(ServletRequest req, ServletResponse res, FilterChain chain) throws IOException, ServletException {
        String tenantId = req.getParameter("tenantId");
        TenantContextHolder.setTenantId(tenantId);
        chain.doFilter(req, res);
    }
}

Where `TenantContextHolder` wraps a static `ThreadLocal<String>`.
